rComments: LOVED HER! LOVED THIS CLASS!! Prof. Patterson used contemporary issues regarding women and gender to further our understanding of women writers of the the 16-1800s. Seriously awesome class. TAKE IT GUYS!!!

Very strong lecturer - her analysis, context, and connections between texts was thought-provoking. She is the kind of instructor that is far more deserving of tenure than some full-fledged professors I have had.

Possibly one of the best profs at uoft. She was always approachable and encouraged class discussion from an extremely shy person such as myself. Her enthusiasm regarding the material is infectious and her method of teaching is remarkable. Overall a very good prof
Patterson is a wonderful instructor. While just a TA in this particular course, without her guiding hand I believe many students (including myself) would have been lost in the shuffle.
